# Complete English Translation
You are Codex GPT-5.4. Directly implement a runnable Windows 11 system tray voice input application in the current workspace. Do not only provide plans, do not leave critical TODOs, and do not use pseudo-code as a substitute. Prioritize "actually working, actually typing text, actually handling Chinese" before pursuing code aesthetics. For points that cannot be 100% reliably implemented in Windows user mode, you must implement a functional fallback and clearly document it in the README; do not pretend to have achieved perfection.

Target Product: A Windows voice input application that resides in the system tray. Hold the hotkey to start recording; release to inject the recognized text into the currently focused input field. Defaults to Simplified Chinese recognition and supports menu-based language switching. When recording, an elegant, refined capsule overlay appears at the bottom-center of the screen, with a real-time volume-driven 5-bar waveform on the left and a live partial transcript on the right. After releasing the hotkey, if LLM refinement is enabled, perform extremely conservative error correction first, then inject the text.

## I. Tech Stack & Project Constraints
1. Use C# 12 + .NET 8 + WPF, targeting Windows 11 23H2+.
2. The project must be a native Windows desktop application; do not use Electron, Tauri, MAUI, or WebView wrappers.
3. Launch in system tray resident mode; no main window, no taskbar entry, no Alt+Tab entry.
4. Use single-instance mode; repeated launches should activate the existing instance instead of spawning a second process.
5. Recommended libraries (avoid over-reliance on fancy frameworks):
   - `NAudio`: Microphone capture and real-time RMS
   - `H.NotifyIcon.Wpf`: System tray icon
   - `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`: MVVM pattern
   - `Whisper.net` or a viable .NET wrapper for `whisper.cpp`: Local multilingual speech recognition
6. All critical features must have real implementations: global hotkeys, recording, partial transcript, overlay animations, clipboard injection, IME switching, LLM refine, settings persistence.
7. Clean code structure with service-layer separation; do not place all logic in App.xaml.cs or a single massive Window.

## II. Push-to-Talk & Recording Behavior
1. Product-wise, prioritize "hold Fn to talk, release Fn to inject text".
2. Face Windows reality: Fn is a firmware-level key on most machines; user-mode applications cannot reliably receive it via standard low-level keyboard hooks.
3. Therefore, you must design as follows:
   - Implement an abstract `IPushToTalkTrigger`.
   - First attempt best-effort Fn detection (Raw Input / vendor scancode / observable low-level hook paths).
   - If Fn cannot be reliably detected on the current machine, automatically fall back to a configurable, globally hookable, suppressible hotkey (default: `Right Ctrl`).
   - The tray menu or settings UI must clearly display the currently active PTT key.
4. When holding the active PTT key:
   - Start recording
   - Show overlay
   - Start real-time partial transcript
5. When releasing the PTT key:
   - Stop recording
   - Finalize full transcription
   - If LLM refinement is enabled and configured, show `Refining...` and await result
   - Finally inject text into the focused input field
6. Suppress the active PTT key from propagating to the foreground application where possible, to avoid triggering host app shortcuts or input anomalies.
7. Toggle-to-record (press once to start, press again to stop) is forbidden; must be hold-to-talk, release-to-finish.

## III. Speech Recognition & Languages
1. Default language must be Simplified Chinese; out-of-box Chinese recognition is mandatory.
2. Provide language switching in the menu:
   - English
   - Simplified Chinese
   - Traditional Chinese
   - Japanese
   - Korean
3. Persist the current language selection; restore after app restart.
4. Prioritize local multilingual Whisper for recognition backend because:
   - Works offline without cloud dependency
   - More stable for mixed Chinese-English
   - Better for out-of-box desktop tools
5. Do not embed large model files directly in the repo; implement a usable model management strategy:
   - Preferred: Auto-download default multilingual model on first launch to `%LocalAppData%\<AppName>\Models`
   - Alternative: Provide `scripts/download-model.ps1` + in-app missing prompt + one-click trigger
   - Do not require users to manually follow documentation
6. Must provide partial transcript during recognition, not only full result on release.
7. Even if the underlying implementation uses incremental chunk decoding, the user must see continuously updating text.
8. Special handling for mixed Chinese-English:
   - Default language is `zh`
   - Do not mistranscribe obvious English tech terms into Chinese homophones
   - Partial / final transcript text stitching must be stable, not jittery

